Devices and methods of for wireless communication in a
directional multi-gigabit (DMG) band are generally
described. A device can detect a starting point of an awake
window (AW). The device can encode a first announcement
traffic indication message (ATIM) for directional transmis-
sion, after no more than a point coordination function (PCF)
interframe space (PIFS) subsequent to the starting point,
over a first beamformed link to a first station (STA). The
device can encode a second ATIM for directional transmis-
sion subsequent to directional transmission of the first
ATIM, within the AW and in a different direction than the
directional transmission of the first ATIM, over a second
beamformed link to a second STA. Other devices, systems
and methods are also described.
